shared_text:
US National Weather Service Kansas City Missouri
January 10, 2019 at 8:44 PM ¬∑

Folks have asked for timing graphics. We thought it was a good idea, so here it is. Precipitation is expected to lift northward from tomorrow morning into the afternoon. The farther north and east it gets, into northeastern Missouri mainly, the better chance it'll be in the form of snow. That transition area, and eventually the all snow area, will spread westward through afternoon and evening. By 8 to 9 PM, tomorrow, everyone should have transitioned to all snow.

This adorable little kitten came to Medicine Creek Furniture store in Unionville last Friday.
He/she was quite frightened at first, and learned to escape us underneath beds, tables, and found HUNDREDS of places to hide here, but I finally caught the little cutie on Sunday afternoon!
WE NEED A HOME FOR IT, as our Husky LOVES stuffed animals, and would see this little one as such!
Call Shirley...660 748 5964.
I now have it litter box trained, eating canned food and water, and will come out from hiding, and LOVES to be held and purrs so sweetly!

HAS TO BE INSIDE, it's so small...couldn't survive w/o a Mama outside!
FREE to someone who will love it!!!
